    • Method Detail

      • getCompetitorList

        org.w3c.dom.Document getCompetitorList(YFSEnvironment env,
                                       org.w3c.dom.Document inXML)
                                throws com.yantra.yfs.japi.YFSException,
                                       java.rmi.RemoteException

        The getCompetitorList API gets the Competitor list. API is capable of finding Competitors defined in the system depending upon the inputs passed.

        Related Documents
        Input XML Input DTD Output XML Output DTD Error XML Error DTD

        User Exits:

          com.yantra.pca.ycd.japi.ue.YCDgetCompetitorListUE
            This user exit is called to get the Competitor List. The error code YCD00035 is thrown if an exception occurs during the invocation of this user exit.

          Events Raised: None

          Audits: None

          Pre Conditions: None

          Post Conditions: None

          Output Template Support: Yes

          Additional Information
          This UserExit is not implemented

        Parameters:
        env - Required. Environment handle returned by the createEnvironment API.
        inXML - Required. For more information, see the associated input xml files.

        Returns:
        A XML document that contains the list of Competitors. refer to the associated output files.

        Throws:
        com.yantra.yfs.japi.YFSException - Exception containing error codes in the standard error files.
        java.rmi.RemoteException - Java's default remote exception handler.
